Package: fetchx
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: A blazing-fast, feature-rich system information tool
 FetchX is a modern neofetch replacement written in Rust. It displays
 system information with ASCII art or images in the terminal.
 .
 Features:
  - Blazing fast (10-50ms vs neofetch's 200-500ms)
  - 5 image backends (kitty, sixel, chafa, w3m, iterm2)
  - Smart image caching with random images
  - 60+ distro logos
  - Nerd Font icons support
  - Progress bars for memory and disk
  - JSON output for scripting
  - Daemon mode for status bars
